title: Ukrainian Grain on Cargo Ship Reaches Romania
description: After a journey of 12 hours across waters caught up in the war, a ship carrying tons of wheat made it safely to Romanian waters, as Kyiv worked to transport grain overland, as well.

title: Zelensky, at U.N., Urges World Leaders to Help Ukraine
description: Painting Vladimir Putin’s Russia as a nation that seeks to dominate others, President Volodymyr Zelensky cast his appeal for broad support as a matter of global security.

title: Wednesday Briefing: Zelensky’s Warning at the U.N.
description: Plus, new discoveries about a nomadic clan on the island of Borneo.

title: An Operatic Mess at the San Carlo Theater
description: The San Carlo in Naples is at the center of an offstage drama in which each of two respected figures believes he is the house’s rightful leader.

title: Trudeau Rejects India’s Denial of Involvement of Assassination in Canada
description: The Canadian prime minister again urged India to cooperate with the investigation into the death of a Sikh separatist.

title: Britain Passes Sweeping New Online Safety Law
description: The far-reaching bill had set off debates about balancing free speech and privacy rights against efforts to halt the spread of harmful content online.

title: Ukraine’s Counteroffensive Looms Large as Zelensky Addresses U.N.
description: The effort to drive Russian forces from Ukraine’s south and east has been slow and bloody. Here’s a look at what might come next in the campaign.

title: East Libya’s Leader Keeps Tight Control Over Flood Aid
description: Khalifa Hifter, who oversees a military dictatorship that rules the eastern half of the divided, oil-rich nation, is dominating the response to the disaster and could use it to further entrench his power.

title: Who Was Hardeep Singh Nijjar? Canada Says India Was Behind His Killing
description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada accused Indian agents of involvement in the killing of a Sikh separatist in British Columbia. Who was he?

title: Ancient Earthworks Trodden by Golfers Become a World Heritage Site
description: The UNESCO World Heritage Committee has recognized the Octagon Earthworks in central Ohio as a cultural marvel.

title: In Switzerland, Ex-Soldier Faces Trial Over Disappearances in Belarus
description: A former security services official is charged with helping to abduct three men in Minsk in 1999. He’s being tried in Switzerland under universal jurisdiction.

title: Biden Aides and Saudis Explore Defense Treaty Modeled After Asian Pacts
description: Despite U.S. fatigue over Middle East wars, the White House sees a security agreement resembling those with Japan or South Korea as an incentive for Saudi Arabia to normalize relations with Israel.

title: Russia Drone Attack in Lviv Kills 1, Ukrainian Officials Say
description: One of the attacks, in the western city of Lviv, far from the front line, killed one person and caused fires at warehouses, including one storing humanitarian aid, officials said.

title: Canada’s Allegation Against India Punctuates Tension Over Separatists
description: The allegation that India was involved in the killing of a Sikh leader in Canada came after New Delhi had accused Western countries of inaction on secessionist groups.

title: Yemen Gets Ownership of Artifacts, but Met Will Still Display Them
description: Ownership of the artifacts is being restored to Yemen, but given the civil war there Yemeni officials have asked the museum to safeguard them for now through a custodial agreement.

title: U.N. General Assembly: Nations Gather in Shadow of Russia’s War and Host of Urgent Issues
description: President Biden will call for continued support for Ukraine, President Volodymyr Zelensky plans to appear in person in New York City to shore up support, and leaders of key countries are skipping this year’s event.

title: Keir Starmer Meets Emmanuel Macron, Building European Ties
description: Keir Starmer, the Labour Party leader, visited the French president just days after a high-profile gathering in Montreal. But efforts to improve European ties in the wake of Brexit could be fraught.

title: Azerbaijan Says Military Operation Underway in Nagorno-Karabakh
description: The Azerbaijani Defense Ministry said it had begun “local anti-terrorist operations” against an Armenian enclave, raising fears of a new armed conflict.

title: What Is the U.N. General Assembly?
description: This body, which meets annually, has seen its influence wane over the years, but it is still considered important to global affairs.

title: Wall Street Journal Reporter Evan Gershkovich Appears in Russian Court
description: The American, whom Russia accuses of espionage, is appealing a ruling that extended his pretrial detention. The United States has said he is wrongfully detained.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Cargo Ship Defies Russian Threats and Exits Ukrainian Port With Wheat
description: Russia had warned that it would view vessels as a military threat. The ship was headed toward Romanian waters.

title: Australia Officially Declares Arrival of El Niño
description: The authorities ordered school closures on the south coast of New South Wales, where springtime temperatures were expected to near 100 degrees.

title: Tuesday Briefing
description: Changes in the Ukrainian defense ministry.

title: Load. Fire. Get to Cover.
description: It was just a single moment in a war that at times feels endless, but an image of Ukrainian soldiers firing upon an unseen enemy captures the dangers of the front line.

title: Biden to Urge Nations to Protect and Nurture Democracy
description: In a speech to the United Nations, President Biden is expected to promote his administration’s achievements around the globe even as he confronts challenges at home.
